<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p>Canadian Adventure tour connects Vancouver on the Pacific Ocean with the untamed grandeur of the Canadian Rockies aboard the famous Rocky Mountaineer train. We start with five nights in Vancouver before boarding the train for a spectacular two day journey to the Rockies. We spend four nights in the friendly frontier town of Jasper with time to enjoy its wide choice of excursions, walking and wildlife. We continue to Banff along the spell binding Icefields Parkway with its lofty peaks, hanging glaciers and turquoise lakes. Our final four nights are spent in the lively town of Banff. Here you’ll find a wealth of shops, outdoor activities and guided excursions. You must visit beautiful Lake Moraine and Lake Louise. In each resort an Inghams Representative will be on hand to help you enjoy your holiday to the full.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p><strong>3 Nights Vancouver</strong> Fly to Vancouver with a short transfer to your downtown hotel. Enjoy a walk around Stanley Park, Chinatown, historic Gastown or the shops along Robson Street. A wide range of optional excursions include scenic cruises or a Float Plane flight and whale watching trips through the Gulf Islands to Victoria on Vancouver Island.</p>
<p><strong>1 Night, Rocky Mountaineer</strong> All aboard the world-famous Rocky Mountaineer Journey through the clouds for a spectacular two day rail journey to the Rockies. First day highlights include Hells gate in Fraser canyon, an overnight stop in Kamloops. Our second day enters the dramatic Caribou and Monashee mountains, with glaciers, waterfalls and wildlife before passing Mount Robson the highest peak in the Canadian Rockies. We arrive late afternoon into Jasper.</p>
<p><strong>4 or 5 Nights, Jasper National Park</strong> Located in the Rockies’ largest National Park, Jasper town has a welcoming frontier atmosphere and offers endless excursion, recreational and walking opportunities. Don’t miss a scenic cruise on Maligne Lake, white-water rafting, or a hike to Angel Glacier at Cavell Meadows. </p>
<p><strong>5 or 6 Nights Banff National Park</strong> Start with a spellbinding trip along the 230km Icefields Parkway stopping at Columbia Glacier enroute for lunch (included). We arrive in the lively town of Banff with its many shops and excursion choices, including the gondola and hot-springs, Johnston Canyon, Moraine Lake and Lake Louise.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>What’s included</h2>
<ul>
<li>Return flights from the UK</li>
<li>Scenic transfers between resorts, to/from the train stations, from/to Vancouver and Calgary airports</li>
<li>2 day Rocky Mountaineer train journey in Red Leaf</li>
<li>Hotel rooms in either all 3 Star, all 4 Star or all 5 Star Hotels</li>
<li>Hotel meals Deluxe hot and cold buffet breakfast included in all 5 Star Fairmont hotels,except Whistler which is on room only. All 3 and 4 Star hotels are on room only</li>
<li>Inghams Representative in each resort</li>
</ul>
